Design and Development of Intelligent Decision-making System for Freight Station Marketing in Xi’an Railway Group
FU Xiaofeng1, FAN Xinlong2, LIU Lining3
(1. School of Transportation, Xi’an Railway Vocational & Technical Institute, Xi’an 710014, Shaanxi, China; 2. School of Electronics and Information, Xi’an Railway Vocational & Technical Institute, Xi’an 710014, Shaanxi, China; 3. Freight Transportation Department, China Railway Xi’an Group Co., Ltd , Xi’an 710054, Shaanxi, China)
Abstract: Customer management of the existing marketing management system of Xi’an Railway Group needs to be strengthened, and logistics service decision-making level and market response ability require to be improved to meet the diversified needs of customs. To this end, on the basis of depth analysis of the problems in the existing marketing management system, this paper constructed the goal and architecture of the intelligent marketing decision-making system for the freight station in Xi’an Railway Group. Intelligent analysis and decision-making technologies such as big data, MIDSS, GIS and Beidou navigation were comprehensively utilized to design and develop the system, break through information barriers between industries, and deeply excavate the relevant internal and external data. Combining historical information, this paper analyzed, integrated, and processed the data to facilitate the decisionmaking functions of marketing analysis and management, supply and demand market prediction and early warning, customer analysis and management, and marketing and logistics scheme. The research provides technical support for Xi’an Railway Group to integrate the logistics resources of various freight stations in the region, analyze customers’ personalized needs, accurately match marketing strategies, make real-time marketing decisions, and improve freight service quality and market competitiveness. Keywords: Railway Freight station; Big Data Technology; Marketing Management; Precision Marketing; Intelligent Decision-Making
29

